Privacy Policy
Last updated: July 23, 2024

Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how Bookshelf ("we", "our", or "us"), operated by Asynchro, collects, uses, and discloses your information when you use our mobile application ("App").

1. Information We Collect
1.1 Personal Information

When you sign in to our App using your Google account, we collect your email address and user ID. This information is used to authenticate your account and provide you access to the App.

1.2 Usage Information

We collect information about your usage of the App, including:

The books you scan and add to your library
The books you lend to others
Reading status of your books
Any other interactions with the App
1.3 Device Information

We may collect information about your device, including:

Device type and model
Operating system
Unique device identifiers
Mobile network information
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect to:

Provide and improve the App
Personalize your experience
Send notifications related to lending and reading statuses
Maintain the security and integrity of the App
Conduct analytics to understand how the App is used and improve its functionality
3. Sharing Your Information
We do not share your personal information with third parties except in the following circumstances:

With your consent
To comply with legal obligations
To protect and defend our rights and property
To prevent or investigate possible wrongdoing in connection with the App
With service providers who assist us in operating the App, provided they agree to keep your information confidential
4. Data Security
We implement appropriate security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. We strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information but cannot guarantee its absolute security.

5. Data Retention
We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to provide the App and fulfill the purposes described in this Privacy Policy. We may also retain and use your information to comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements.

6. Your Data Protection Rights
You have the right to:

Access, update, or delete your personal information
Object to the processing of your personal information
Request the restriction of processing your personal information
Withdraw your consent at any time
To exercise these rights, please contact us at keshavasilva@gmail.com.

7. Children's Privacy
Our App is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that we have inadvertently received personal information from a child under 13, we will delete such information from our records.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. You are advised to review this Privacy
